libsodium
------------------------------------------
NaCl (pronounced 'salt') is a new easy-to-use high-speed software library for
network communication, encryption, decryption, signatures, etc.

NaCl's goal is to provide all of the core operations needed to build
higher-level cryptographic tools.

Sodium is a portable, cross-compilable, installable, packageable fork of NaCl,
with a compatible API.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.2.1-1
  libsodium-devel-1.0.6-1bl1
  libsodium17-1.0.6-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-2
  cygport-0.20.2-1
  gcc-core-4.9.3-1
  libtool-2.4.6-2
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/jedisct1/libsodium

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/jedisct1/libsodium/archive/1.0.6.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libsodium-1.0.6-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libsodium-1.0.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libsodium-1.0.6-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsodium-1.0.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsodium17-1.0.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsodium-devel-1.0.6-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

